result.execSummary:
The defendant Alonzo L Lacy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Alonzo L Lacy in court with Student Intern Amanda Toonen under the supervision of attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.

As to Count 1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the Defendant guilty and enters judgment of conviction into the record forthwith. 

As to Count 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Count 2 DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.

Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties.  As to Count 1: 
The court sentenced the defendant to 3 months in the House of Correction with credit for 1 day time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 12 months.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
-10 days in the House of Correction as Condition Time, STAYED, to be used at the agent's discretion.
-Anger management program.
-Obtain GED/HSED.
-No further violations of the law. 
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges during period of probation, failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. 

Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.

Attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer in court, defendant Alonzo L Lacy not in court, in custody, not produced.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea and sentencing in Branch 46. jks
  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for 04-15-2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  
Defendant to have no contact with: Felicia L. DJB (7/21/2013); Javon L; Latika JD.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Alonzo L Lacy in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Defendant Alonzo L Lacy in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Branch 46.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for February 25, 2015 at 08:30 am.
